OL,3,CThe PE teacher who ran 10km every day
OL,4,Cfor a year to honour his Grandfather
OL,6,F"It seemed like a great idea at the
OL,7,Ftime but after three weeks I was
OL,8,Fthinking I can't be doing this."
OL,10,FWhile it was far from easy, Phill said
OL,11,Fit was his pupils at St Michael's that
OL,12,Fgot him through each day.
OL,14,FHe said: "When I say I've completed
OL,15,Fit, I really mean we've completed it
OL,16,Fbecause I wouldn't have got through
OL,17,Fsome stages if it wasn't for the
OL,18,Fchildren... They'd come in to school
OL,19,Fand high five me and ask me how my
OL,20,Ffeet were. They just kept me going."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
